[[Image:Same-sex marriage in San Francisco City Hall 20080617.jpg|thumb|thumb|right|Civil [[same-sex marriage]] ceremony being performed in [[San Francisco]] City Hall.]]
'''Same-sex marriage in the United States''' is recognized in several jurisdictions. As of November 2012, nine states&mdash;[[Same-sex marriage in Connecticut|Connecticut]], [[Same-sex marriage in Iowa|Iowa]], [[Same-sex marriage in Maine|Maine]], [[Same-sex marriage in Maryland|Maryland]], [[Same-sex marriage in Massachusetts|Massachusetts]], [[Same-sex marriage in New Hampshire|New Hampshire]], [[Same-sex marriage in New York|New York]], [[Same-sex marriage in Vermont|Vermont]], and [[Same-sex marriage in Washington|Washington]]&mdash;as well as the [[Same-sex marriage in the District of Columbia|District of Columbia]] and two [[Same-sex marriage under United States tribal jurisdictions|Native American tribes]]<ref>[[Coquille Indian Tribe|Coquille]] and [[Suquamish tribe|Suquamish]]</ref>&mdash;have legalized same-sex marriage. In addition, [[Same-sex marriage in Rhode Island|Rhode Island]] recognizes same-sex marriages performed in other jurisdictions,<ref name="freedomtomarry1">{{cite web|url=http://www.freedomtomarry.org/states/ |title=States |publisher=Freedom to Marry |date=April 16, 2010 |accessdate=June 27, 2010}}</ref><ref name=riex>The situation in the state is uncertain, despite an opinion by the state's Attorney General:
*{{cite news |work=New York Times |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/02/22/us/22rhode.html |first=Katie |last=Zezima |title=Rhode Island Steps Toward Recognizing Same-Sex Marriage |date=February 22, 2007 |accessdate=July 3, 2011 |quote=Mr. Lynch said his interpretation permitted recognition of the marriages, although he acknowledged that it was just an opinion and did not have the force of law}}
*{{cite web |publisher=Human Rights Campaign |url=http://www.hrc.org/laws-and-legislation/entry/rhode-island-marriage-relationship-recognition-law|title=Rhode Island Marriage/Relationship Recognition Law |accessdate=July 19, 2012 |quote=This is not a binding opinion and the attorney general noted that this question will most likely be answered by the courts}}
*{{cite web |url=http://www.marriageequalityri.org/www/learn/marriage_faq/ |title=Marriage FAQ |publisher=Marriage Equality Rhode Island |accessdate=July 3, 2011 |quote=it is still a complicated issue about whether these marriages will be respected in Rhode Island.}}
*{{cite web |publisher=GLAD |url=http://www.glad.org/uploads/docs/publications/ri-marriage-guide.pdf |title=Marriage Guide for Rhode Island Same-Sex Couples |page=88 |quote=legal uncertainty remains in this area |accessdate=July 3, 2011 |format=PDF}}</ref> and [[Same-sex marriage in California|California]], which briefly granted same-sex marriages in 2008, now recognizes them on a conditional basis.<ref>See
